{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b432596e-1e5c-49dc-956b-c941157d9250","content":"Here are the issues I found in this `template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** (required) — every template must have a unique `\"identity\"` field.\n\n2. **`defaultValue` not in `choices`** (line 10) — `targetFramework` defaults to `\"net7.0\"`, but the only choices are `\"net8.0\"` and `\"net9.0\"`.\n\n3. **Invalid int default** (line 24) — `maxRetries` has `datatype: \"int\"` but `defaultValue` is `\"abc\"`.\n\n4. **`choices` format** (lines 11–14) — the `choices` field for a `choice` parameter should be an array of objects (e.g., `[{\"choice\":\"net8.0\",\"description\":\".NET 8\"}]`), not a dictionary keyed by value.\n\n5. **Missing `value` on computed symbol** (line 27) — `computed` symbols require a `\"value\"` expression.\n\n6. **Missing `generator` on generated symbol** (line 30) — `generated` symbols require a `\"generator\"` field (e.g., `\"guid\"`).\n\n7. **Missing `actionId` in postAction** (line 35) — post actions need an `\"actionId\"` to identify which action to run (e.g., `\"210D431B-A78B-4D2F-B762-4ED3E3EA9025\"` for dotnet restore).\n\n8. **`shortName` collision risk** — `\"restore\"` is a common CLI verb and may conflict with `dotnet restore`.\n\nWould you like me to fix these issues?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b229c0cf-06b1-4015-a9b3-8248985bab88","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"7407:48F1C:1C8B043:1F93954:69FA90E5"},"id":"f0c0a305-8e5b-4643-8b5c-aab5bb06cc1f","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:02.849Z","parentId":"7cdf9b92-4d57-4dd7-a874-2bd1f1d3b9fb"}
